A love story: Beans + Chef Hak’s BBQ sauce 🫘❤️ 

BBQ Baked beans 
Ingredients: 
2 cans pinto beans, drained and rinsed
1 can kidney beans, drained and rinsed 
10 ounces of bacon, cut into small pieces 
1 yellow onion, diced 
½ cup Chef Hak’s BBQ sauce @wholefoods 
½ cup ketchup 
½ cup coconut sugar 
1 tablespoon yellow mustard
1 tablespoon worcestershire sauce 

Instructions: 
Cook the bacon and onion in a skillet over medium heat. Saute until the bacon is crispy and the onions are tender. 
While the bacon cooks, rinse the beans and add them to the crockpot with the BBQ sauce, ketchup, coconut sugar, mustard, and worcestershire sauce. 
Add the cooked bacon and onions to the crockpot and mix well. 
Cook on high for 3 hours and enjoy!

Easy breezy summertime dinner recipe unlocked ☀️🔐 

Summer Squash Skillet: 

Ingredients: 
1 package Chef Hak’s chicken meatballs @costco 
1 8-ounce package of pasta
2 zucchini or summer squash, thinly sliced
1 small shallot, thinly sliced 
2 cloves of garlic, minced 
1 bunch of basil 
1 tbsp avocado oil
½ tsp salt, more to taste
grated parmesan for serving

Instructions: 
Bring a large pot of water to a boil and cook the pasta according to the package. 
Preheat 1 tbsp avocado oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add the zucchini, shallot, and garlic to the pan, sauteing until tender. 
Transfer half of the zucchini mixture to a food processor with ½ cup of pasta water, basil, and salt. Pulse in the food processor until smooth. 
Add the Chef Hak’s meatballs to the skillet with the zucchini, and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, until browned. 
Add the cooked pasta to the skillet, top with the blended sauce, and mix well.
Top with parmesan and enjoy!
